fr.pinguet62.jsfring.gui

Class AbstractCrudBean<T extends Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.pinguet62.jsfring.gui.AbstractBean<T>
      • fr.pinguet62.jsfring.gui.AbstractSelectableBean<T>
        • fr.pinguet62.jsfring.gui.AbstractCrudBean<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of objects to display.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProfilesBean, UsersBean

    public abstract class AbstractCrudBean<T extends Serializable>
extends AbstractSelectableBean<T>
    AbstractSelectableBean with CRUD operations on selected value.

    Before each action, the selected value is initialized with chosen value, and action are performed on him.

    See Also:
    AbstractService.create(Serializable), AbstractService.get(Serializable), AbstractService.update(Serializable), AbstractService.delete(Serializable), Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public void create()
        Create new value.
        Call when the user click on Submit button into Create view.

        The initial selected value is the new value set by calling preCreate() before showing the create view .

        Refresh list after creation.

        See Also:
        preCreate(), AbstractService.create(Serializable)

      • delete

        Refresh list after deletion.

      • postDelete

        protected void postDelete()
        Fix LazyDataModel count after deletion:
        For lazy loading, after deletion of only row of last page, the page is empty because DataTable thinks the current page is the same. So the row count is decremented to permit the return to the previous page.
        See Also:
        LazyDataModel.setRowCount(int)

      • preCreate

        public void preCreate()
        Initialize the process of creation by setting new value.
        See Also:

      • update

        public void update()
        Update the selected value.
        Call when the user click on Submit button into Update view.

        Refresh list after update.
